I have been passing/stopping by this Dunkin Donuts for years on my way to work. Never had any issue really. Over the last say 6 months or so service speed has been awful. Around New years one visit their kitchen was closed (thats fine) gave them another try the next day and they have one employee on that shift buried in orders. Multiple times I have waited through the drive thru lane that would usually take 5-6 minutes that took 15-20 minutes or longer. Been to Dunkins 100's of times and cant remember waiting over 5-10 minutes during the busiest times at any location. This location takes 5 minutes just to greet at the ordering intercom. Today was horrid, a driver behind me was yelling  out their window to get out of the way because the intercom attendant was taking forever. Got in the lane around 642am-out of the lane at 658am (one car in front of me, maybe one already at the window) all to be asked to park and wait for 2 wake up wraps.  3-5 minutes go by had to run in and get them myself, line was 4-5 people all who looked just as frustrated, again employees were super friendly so I dont think that's the issue at this location. 20 minutes for a med coffee and 2 wake up wraps is an issue.
